gomodel:SYNGO_4671  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 5: Endogenous Exo70 is associated to synapse junctions. The brains from 12 weeks-old rats were fractionated by differential centrifugation. Exo70 is present in ELKS2-positive, Synaptohysin-negative PSD fraction.\n\nFig. 6: Endogenous Exo70 is found in both pre- and postsynaptic compartments: Rat hippocampal neurons were fixed at DIV 21 and immuno-stained for Exo70. Co-localization was observed with SHANK2 (post) and Bassoon (pre). No quantification. Exo70 puncta were also present without Shank2 or Bassoon colocalization. Experimental description: M&M: hippocampi were dissected from embryonic Sprague-Dawley rats (E18). Neurons were dissociated with trypsin and plated\n\nantibody;\nrabbit Exo70 1:1000 (Proteintech, USA)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2022-07-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4671" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

